She has candour for doing good things, and since she came on board as a Consular of the United States of America (USA) to Nigeria, she has made many exploits between the countries. And these have closed the ties between these two great nations. Her many feats in the areas of agriculture, health, education, empowerment and sundry sectors are too numerous to mention. The inauguration of the HIV Trust Fund in Abuja, the event created an opportunity to bring the country’s dynamic sector into efforts to expand domestic investment in HIV control. Even with the re-introduction of ‘Drop Box’ for visa renewal, has attracted much applause from many Nigerians, as she has turned around the commission transparently. Ambassador Leonard, who was appointed to Nigeria in 2019 by former President Donald Trump, speaks French, Spanish, Afrikaans, and Dutch is a native of Massachusetts, graduated magna cum laude with a B.A. from Boston University, with a major in economics and a minor in French. In 1988, she earned a master’s degree in international relations, with an emphasis on African Studies, from the Johns Hopkins University School of Advanced International Studies. In 2004, she received a Master of Security and Strategic Studies from the U.S. Naval War College, with distinction.